											 SQL Server and the “Lock pages in memory” Right in Windows Server 					
					 
						 Posted on   February 14, 2011 						 by   Glenn Berry   					 

					 
						 Another Windows setting you  might  want to enable is “Lock pages in memory”. There is some controversy within the SQL Server community and within Microsoft about whether and when you should enable this setting. Before you decide whether you want to do this, let me give you some background. When SQL Server 2005 